  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The book \"Translation Policies in Legal and Institutional Settings,\" published by Leuven University Press in 2021, explores crucial aspects of translation policy within legal frameworks. Despite currently having no public mentions or citations, it holds potential significance given its relevance to sustainability and policy discussions.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Published in 2021, \"Translation Policies in Legal and Institutional Settings\" delves into the intricate relationship between translation and policy within various legal and institutional contexts. The academic relevance of this work is underscored by its capability to address pressing sustainability issues, as indicated by its association with the Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs).</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">While the book has yet to garner citations or public discourse across significant platforms, it is important to note the inferred strength in its commercial linkage, evidenced by listings on major retailers like Amazon and Goodreads. This suggests potential avenues for reaching broader audiences and engaging with readers interested in its thematic focus.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The lack of active community discussion\u2014reflected in the absence of mentions on social media or educational platforms\u2014presents both a challenge and an opportunity. The work\u2019s themes surrounding legal translation policies are timely, suggesting that future scholarly engagement could illuminate its relevance in practical applications and policy development.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Although initial uptake has been limited, the groundwork laid by this book paves the way for further investigation into how translation policies shape and influence institutional mechanisms. The insights provided could serve as a catalyst for future studies and contribute substantially to the ongoing dialogue about the role of translation in legal contexts.</p>",
